result.name: Tai Wing Wah Restaurant

reviews.text: Traditional Canton Yam-cha, delicious because of authentic ingredients used
HK local yummy dim sum and hakka style food 😋

It is a great place catch up on old traditional Hong Kong Chinese dishes that are mostly lost in other restaurants. It serves dishes that aren't modernly healthy, in other words, the dishes are full of salt and lard and made what they have been meant to be from day one when the dishes were invented I guess! Highly recommended especially for nostalgic reason.
The lard rice is absolutely the BESTEST! It is fat, it is oily, but it is simply delicious. Definitely love it. I’ll come again.
Food so-so, price raise a lot and not cheap , when we left at night , a mouse ran out near my table and keep running around the table , scary situation
